When American Ice Company first opened, it was the coolest thing. It's on the edge of U Street so you felt like you stumbled upon a hidden gem. The decor is unique and half the restaurant is outside heated with heat lamps during the winter. The service is good and the food fine. That's where I give it a three star. The food isn't amazing, but it does it's job. It comes out on a cheap paper plate and is smaller in portions but you pay DC prices for it. They have an okay beer list and have Crispin hard cider in a can. Four years ago, it was the bee's knees of DC, but now it's another average restaurant for locals to hang out in.
It's a cool spot, but gets too crowded, and personally nothing really sets it apart from other bars.
I love their swatchoes. They're honestly the only reason I go their.

American Ice is a little oasis of simplicity in the heart of the city. There's a great beer selection (I can always count on them for some Blood Orange IPA) accompanied by an unpretentious hipster vibe. Regarding food, we tried the swachos and enjoyed them as a nice snack.

Stumbled upon this place last night before a show at the 9:30 Club; loved the look of it and the fact that they have outdoor seating; beer selection good but pricey and I don't get the jam jar glass thing? Why is that considered to be the "cool" thing these days? I'd rather drink out of a beer glass, to be honest...The food was a real disappointment, though!! We had the BBQ platter with pork and brisket (and beans and slaw) - the beans were good, the slaw was ok but really needed salt but the meat was anything but good - very dried up, especially the brisket - dry, crumbly pieces...the pork was a little better but rather boring tasting...We continued on to Garden District, where the brisket is out of this world and they serve German beer on draft!! I still liked this place, but it needs improvement on the food front - and maybe better pricing....one buck off just one of the beers on draft for a Happy Hour deal is really not wonderful!!

A nice space for drink specials before going out on U Street - this bar can get somewhat uncomfortable with the smell of cigarettes lingering in the air. The beers on tap are top notch and the comfortable atmosphere is a great place to meet up with friends before taking a night out on the town.
Wants to be hip but trying to hard. Go somewhere else.

Really fun bar that screams out hipster! All of our drinks were served in reused glass jars, which was a cute touch, and the beers on tap were nice and crafty. We ordered some sort of pork nachos appetizer which was the epitome of moreish (as in, the more you eat it, the more you want more).The inside had this reused industrial feel to it, and was a big open space that's perfect for seating big parties or just for an intimate meetup. Choose this place if you need to restore your hipness levels or impress whoever you're meeting

Nice patio and good beer selection.  Although I like drinking out of mason jars, I feel like you get less beer for your money. It's a pretty happening spot so expect it to be crowded and noisy. I like that it's off of the main U street drag and is a little hidden.
The design of the bar is nice. The food and beer are good, but rather expensive. The deal-breaker is the fratty crowd at night.

Love the outdoor patio and that the main bar doors are open in nice weather. The draft beer comes in mason jars and they have good cocktails too. The BBQ is also delicious. Great place to stop on the way to 930 club!
Very relaxed place with good food and drinks. The kitchen is open late and probably some of the best BBQ in town. Drinks come in mason jars which I could do without.
Serves some decent food selections with an Excellent outdoor area with bench seating.   Perfectly situated near 930 club for pregame activities

Ice House is a real hidden treasure in Northwest.  A quick walk from 9:30 Club, this is a great place for pre/post show drinks and food.  The atmosphere and decor are really great and they have a great draft beer menu.  They have a basic barbecue menu, but the food is fantastic.  Check this place out!

I have patronized the American Ice Company a number of times. They have a great selection of beers and provide a nice dose of comfort foods (swachos, brisket sandwich or platter) given their limited kitchen space. Constructed in what looks like an old warehouse, it's great use of an industrial space which opens up to a large patio with picnic tables (of a beer garden-esque style). A definite neighborhood favorite.
